        boolean setNBT(java.lang.String key,
               java.lang.String nbt)
        Set arbitrary NBT. 
        
    var compound = mappet.createCompound();

    compound.setNBT("stack", '{id:"minecraft:diamond",Count:64b}');

    // {stack:{id:"minecraft:diamond",Count:64b}}
    print(compound.stringify());
        Returns:
        Whether given NBT code was successfully was inserted.

      • get

        java.lang.Object get(java.lang.String key)
        Get the value of in this compound by given key of the raw type. Following value types are possible (depending on whatever was found in the compound): INBTCompound, INBTList, String, Double, Long, Float, Int, Short, Byte, or null if the value is absent by given key. 
        
     var tag = mappet.createCompound("{id:\"minecraft:diamond_hoe\",Count:1b}");

     c.send(tag.get("id"));
     c.send(tag.get("Count"));
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the value
        Returns:
        the value found by that key or null

      • equals

        boolean equals(INBTCompound compound)
        Check if this compound is equal to given compound (order of keys doesn't matter). 
        
     var tag1 = mappet.createCompound("{id:\"minecraft:diamond_hoe\",Count:1b}");
     var tag2 = mappet.createCompound("{Count:1b,id:\"minecraft:diamond_hoe\"}");

     c.send(tag1.equals(tag2));
        Parameters:
        compound - the compound to compare with
        Returns:
        whether this compound is equal to the given compound

      • addCompound

        void addCompound(java.lang.String key)
        Adds a new compound to this compound. 
        
    var tag = mappet.createCompound();
    tag.addCompound("compound");
    tag.get("compound").setString("x", "123")
    c.send(tag) //{compound:{x:"123"}}

      • dumpJSON

        java.lang.String dumpJSON()
        Dumps to a JSON String. It first replaces the key-value colons with the proper JSON format. Then, it creates a pattern to match the desired numeric literals and boolean values. It checks if the current matched pattern is "0b" or "1b" and replaces them with "false" and "true" respectively. For the other cases, it removes the last character from the matched pattern, effectively removing the type literal. 
        
   var tag = mappet.createCompound("{id:\"minecraft:diamond_hoe\",Count:1b}");
   c.send(tag.dumpJSON());
